cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.DC, cs.AI. 

The paper is about a new library for machine learning with deep neural networks that focuses on speed. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper specifically mentions support for feed-forward neural networks such as fully-connected ANNs and CNNs, as well as RBMs and Convolutional RBMs, which suggests that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a likely category. Additionally, since CNNs are mentioned, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is another possible category. The paper also discusses software engineering strategies for accelerating runtime, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
